{
  "texts": [
    "Then, the nodes are used to generate Voronoi cells to represent the geometric shape of the lattice particles.",
    "To simulate damaged cases, randomly generated linear cracks are placed in the domain, and corresponding lattice particles are removed accordingly.",
    "Each sample contains 100 × 100 lattice particles.",
    "The wave field is excited by a 1000N load in a short time span (in 3 time steps), and the displacements in the x-and y-direction are recorded for 2000 time steps.",
    "Figure 1 shows the setup for the virtual sensors and their recorded wave field history (in the x-direction)."
  ]
}